www.google.com.ftp.example.org.Root Domain This is the topmost domain in the domain namespace hierarchy. It's label is an "empty string". Top Level DomainThese are subdomains of the root level domain. These TLD names are actually present in the root zone.Secondary Level DomainThese are often created based on the name of a company, product or service. Super domains .com is a super domain of google.comgoogle.com is a super domain of www.google.comSub domainswww.google.com is a sub domain of google.comgoogle.com is a sub domain of .com.Third leveldomainAlso sometimes called as lower level domain, these are used to "denote" what type of server is running. Like for www.google.com it is a WWW server, for ftp.example.org it is an FTP server.The hierarchy doesn't always have to be of order 3.Sometimes we have *.*.co.uk as well, where .uk is the TLD.
